hints.text:
Replace AdministratorAccess with specific policies.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE EC2 policy:

{"Version":"2012-10-17","Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow","Action":["s3:GetObject"],"Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::rimzenberg-static-assets/*"},{"Effect":"Allow","Action":["cloudwatch:PutMetricData"],"Resource":"*"}]}

Minimum output structure.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE:

{"statusCode":200,"body":"{\"order_id\":\"ORD-20251129-001\",\"status\":\"confirmed\"}"}

Minimum working Lambda.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE:

import json,datetime,uuid
def lambda_handler(event,context):
    return {'statusCode':200,'body':json.dumps({'order_id':f'ORD-{str(uuid.uuid4())[:8].upper()}','status':'confirmed','timestamp':datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()+'Z'})}

Postman screenshot must show URL, POST method, 200 OK, JSON body.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE:

Postman: POST to https://abc123.execute-api.eu-west-2.amazonaws.com/orders | 200 OK | {"order_id":"ORD-A3B2","status":"confirmed"}

EC2 web role needs only s3:GetObject and cloudwatch:PutMetricData.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE:

{"Version":"2012-10-17","Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow","Action":["s3:GetObject"],"Resource":"arn:aws:s3:::rimzenberg-static-assets/*"},{"Effect":"Allow","Action":["cloudwatch:PutMetricData"],"Resource":"*"}]}

Use resource-level ARNs not wildcards.

📋 EXPERT SAMPLE RDS policy:

{"Version":"2012-10-17","Statement":[{"Effect":"Allow","Action":["rds-db:connect"],"Resource":"arn:aws:rds-db:eu-west-2:*:dbuser:rimzenberg-rds-prod/*"}]}
